<title>USA: Collins &amp; Aikman raises buyback programme.</title>
<headline>Collins &amp; Aikman raises buyback programme.</headline>
<dateline>CHARLOTTE, N.C. 1997-03-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Collins &amp; Aikman Corp said on Monday that its board had approved increasing its stock purchase programme to $24 million from $12 million in fiscal 1997.</p>
<p>The company, which supplies automotive interior systems, said its bank lenders had also approved the increase.</p>
<p>&quot;The Board continues to believe our stock is an excellent investment, and the repurchase programme will provide shares for the company's employee and director stock option plans,&quot; the company said in a statement.</p>
